 To install a GitHub project locally in Python, you can follow these steps:
 1. Clone the Repository: Open a terminal or command prompt and navigate to the directory where you want to clone the project.
  exampel: git clone https://github.com/username/repository.git
  
2.Install Dependencies: (Check if the project has a requirements.txt file containing the required dependencies.)
pip install -r requirements.txt

3.Run the Project
python main.py

